      },
      "date": "2021-05-11 08:08:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n\nNeil, what is your plan for using/maintaining these ldiskfs patch series for mainline kernels?  Typically, we don't keep separate patch series for *every* kernel, just because it ends up with too many different patches that need to be updated when there is a bug found, or some new patch is added to the series.\n\nIf you are just doing these incrementally so that you can build/test the server code, one reasonable (IMHO) proposal would be to add the new kernel series, then delete the (next-)older series and any unused patches as you are moving to a newer kernel.  It might make sense to keep the series for LTS mainline kernels, since it is more likely those will be adopted by distro kernels.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "1035b11e3de3872d78fd83da41b194d6f4570822",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 143,
        "name": "Yang Sheng",
        "email": "ys@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ys"
      },
      "date": "2021-05-12 04:39:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "6d5d8df7598120307f8548be626845a4a336a544",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 805,
        "name": "Neil Brown",
        "email": "neil@brown.name",
        "username": "neilbrown"
      },
      "date": "2021-05-13 03:42:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Neil, what is your plan for using/maintaining these ldiskfs patch series for mainline kernels? \n\nI had no concrete plan, but your proposal makes lots of sense.   I somewhat lost interest in these patches as they weren't getting any review and I had other things to work on, but if/when the support for newer kernels lands I'm happy to look at removing the support for earlier kernels.\n\nRelatedly:  SUSE always builds KMP (kernel module packages) against the SP release, never against a maintenance update.  So it would suit me if, for SUSE at least, we didn't discard the SP kernel patches when adding support for a maintenance update.  No need for multiple maint update support through.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
